%N A320431 The number of tiles inside a regular n-gon created by lines that run from each of the vertices of the n edges orthogonal to these edges.
%C A320431 Sequence proposed by Thomas Young: draw the regular n-gon and construct 2*n lines that run from both ends of the n edges perpendicular into the n-gon until they hit an opposite edge. (For n even the lines actually hit another vertex, so there are only n additional lines). a(n) is the number of non-overlapping tiles inside the n-gon with edges that are sections of the lines or n-gon edges.
